The Ven a la Luz (meaning Raw Love ) sculpture represents the connection between human beings and nature and the overall aim of it was to raise awareness of the Tulum and Riveria Maya ecosystem. This 33-foot (10 meter) tall artwork was constructed by a talented South African Artist named Daniel Popper The name translates directly as "Come to the Light" in Spanish. This woman sculpture is made with steel, wood, rope, and green plant and features a woman opening her chest cavity to reveal interior full of plants and green vines.

.I had the pleasure of traveling to #Wyoming on my 30 state road trip journey and I couldn’t help but visit this gem! 

.

This beautiful destination is called The Devils Tower it is a truly captivating geological gem with a fascinating history that stretches back millions of years. This iconic rock formation which is also known as “Bear Lodge” by Native American tribes, stands tall in height of 867 feet (264 meters) and has a base circumference of about 1,267 feet & 386 meters 
.
In 1906, Devils Tower was designated as the first national monument in the United States by President Theodore Roosevelt, recognizing its significance as a geological wonder and honoring its cultural importance to the Native American tribes. Since then, it has become a popular destination for rock climbers, adventure seekers, and nature enthusiasts from all over the world. Aka as me lol 
.

Standing in the shadow of Devils Tower, you can’t help but be awestruck by its ancient beauty,  It remains a symbol of resilience and a testament to the forces of nature that shape our world. Visiting this remarkable monument definitely is a humbling experience, reminding one of the interconnectedness between the natural world and human history this is a must visit! Trust me
.

Ah! Yosemite, it is a land cherished by John Muir, the visionary naturalist and conservationist who devoted his life to preserving the wild beauty of nation’s treasures. 🌲✨ John Muir’s deep connection with Yosemite is what led to its protection and paved the way for the birth of the National Park system.
.
In the late 1800s, Muir explored these very landscapes, penning passionate writings that inspired countless others to join the conservation movement. His advocacy led to the establishment of Yosemite National Park in 1890, securing this wonder for generations to come.
.
As you stand among these ancient giants and gaze upon cascading waterfalls, remember the legacy of John Muir, whose love for this place forever changed the course of history. 🏞️💚 #YosemiteLegacy #JohnMuir #NaturePreservation
